{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπαρχή</b>, ἡ, <br /> mostly in <i>plural</i> ἀπαρχαί (compare ἄπαργμα): <br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> <b>beginning of a sacrifice, primal offering</b> (of hairs cut from the forehead), ἀπαρχαὶ κόμης[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 96, compare “Ph.” 1525 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; later, a <b>banquet</b> held on this occasion, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.40b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>firstlings</b> for sacrifice or offering, <b>first-fruits,</b> ἁπάντων ἀπαρχαί[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.71; ἀπαρχὰς ἄγειν θεοῖσι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 183; ἀπαρχὰς θύειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 516; ἀ. σκυλευμάτων “Ph.” 857; ἐπιφέρειν ἀ. τῶν ὡραίων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.58; τῶν ὄντων 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 5.42, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 130, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—so also in <i>singular</i>, λείας ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 761; ἀ. τῶν πατρων χρημάτων 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.92, etc.; ἀνθρώπων ἀ. εἰς Δελφοὺς ἀποστέλλειν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 485; ἀ. ἀπό τινος ἀνατιθέναι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.88; inscribed on votive offerings, [ἀνέθηκεν].. τόδ᾽ α. “IG” 1.382, etc.; frequently in LXX, as LXX.Exo.25.2, +others, cf. NT.Rom.11.16, and _metaphorically_, ἀ. τῶν κεκοιμημένων NT.1Cor.15.20; τῶν κτισμάτων NT.Jam.1.18. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, ἀπαρχαὶ τῶν ἐμῶν προσφθεγμάτων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 402; ἀπαρχὴν τῆς σοφίας ἀνέθεσαν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 343b, etc.; ἀ. ἀπὸ φιλοσοφίας 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.172c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>tax on inheritances,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTaur. 1.7.10\">Refs</a>]; <b>tax</b> paid by Jews, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Stud.Pal.” 4.72 (1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>entrance fee,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTeb. 316.10 (1st c.AD), +others \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>board of officials</b> (compare {ἀπάρχης}), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12(8).273 (from Thasos). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> <b>birth-certificate</b> of a free person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 316.10 (1st c.AD), “PGnom.” 131 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: perhaps <i>metaphorically</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Rom.8.23.\">NT</a>]","strongNumber":"G0536","accentedUnicode":"ἀπαρχή","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G0744","matchingForm":"ἀρχαῖος","stepTransliteration":"archaios","gloss":"ancient","_zh_tw_Gloss":"古人, 古時","_es_Gloss":"antiguo","_zh_Gloss":"古人, 古时"},{"strongNumber":"G0746","matchingForm":"ἀρχή","stepTransliteration":"archē","gloss":"beginning","_zh_tw_Gloss":"起初, 執政","_es_Gloss":"comienzo","_zh_Gloss":"起初, 执政"},{"strongNumber":"G0747","matchingForm":"ἀρχηγός","stepTransliteration":"archēgos","gloss":"founder","_zh_tw_Gloss":"創始者, 元帥","_es_Gloss":"fundador","_zh_Gloss":"创始者, 元帅"},{"strongNumber":"G0757","matchingForm":"ἄρχω","stepTransliteration":"archō","gloss":"be first","_zh_tw_Gloss":"為君王, 要治理","_es_Gloss":"ser el primero","_zh_Gloss":"为君王, 要治理"}],"shortDef":"firstfruits, the first of any crop or livestock offered to God before the rest could be used","mediumDef":"firstfruits, the first of any crop or livestock offered to God before the rest could be used <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>the first act 